5. ✅ Tested with the reproduction bundle – the warning `"mount destination relative-warning-target is not absolute..."` was observed. The subsequent `"rootless container requires user namespaces"` error is an environment limitation (missing user namespace support), which the validation notes specify should be treated as an environment failure, not a reproduction failure.
6. ✅ Collected the git diff – shown below.

